label.value: lysozyme inhibitor activity

definition.value: Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a lysozyme, an enzyme that hydrolyses the beta- (1,4) glycosidic bond between N-acetylmuramic acid and N-acetylglucosamine in peptidoglycan.

label.value: regulation of transcription initiation from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of a process involved in starting transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription initiation from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of a process involved in starting transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: germ plasm

definition.value: Differentiated cytoplasm associated with a pole of an oocyte, egg or early embryo that will be inherited by the cells that will give rise to the germ line.

label.value: GTP cyclohydrolase I regulator activity

definition.value: Modulates the activity of GTP cyclohydrolase I. GTP cyclohydrolase I activity catalyzes the reaction -  GTP + 2 H2O -eq- formate + 2-amino-4-hydroxy-6-(erythro-1,2,3-trihydroxypropyl)-dihydropteridine triphosphate.

label.value: photoreceptor inner segment membrane

definition.value: The membrane surrounding the outer segment of a vertebrate photoreceptor. The photoreceptor inner segment contains mitochondria, ribosomes and membranes where opsin molecules are assembled and passed to be part of the outer segment discs.

label.value: fertilization envelope

definition.value: A structure that lies outside the plasma membrane and surrounds the egg. The fertilization envelope forms from the vitelline membrane after fertilization as a result of cortical granule release.

label.value: vitelline envelope

definition.value: A glycoprotein-based structure that lies outside the plasma membrane and surrounds the egg before fertilization.

label.value: yolk

definition.value: The cytoplasmic part that serves as a nutrient reserve or energy source for the developing embryo.

label.value: yolk plasma

definition.value: Discrete structures that partition the water-soluble portion of the yolk of oocytes and ova, which may or may not be membrane enclosed.

label.value: peptidyl-dipeptidase inhibitor activity

definition.value: Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a peptidyl-dipeptidase. Peptidyl-dipeptidase activity catalyzes the release of C-terminal dipeptides from a polypeptide chain.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription involved in egg activation

definition.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of transcription as a part of the process of egg activation.

label.value: cortical granule

definition.value: A secretory vesicle that is stored under the cell membrane of an egg. These vesicles fuse with the egg plasma membrane as part of egg activation and are part of the block to polyspermy.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter involved in lung bud formation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter that contributes to the branching morphogenesis by which the initial primordium of the lung is formed.

label.value: positive regulation of DNA-templated transcription, termination

definition.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of DNA-templated transcription termination, the process in which transcription is completed -  the formation of phosphodiester bonds ceases, the RNA-DNA hybrid dissociates, and RNA polymerase releases the DNA.

label.value: negative regulation of DNA-templated transcription, termination

definition.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of DNA-dependent transcription termination, the process in which transcription is completed -  the formation of phosphodiester bonds ceases, the RNA-DNA hybrid dissociates, and RNA polymerase releases the DNA.

label.value: nucleoside-triphosphatase regulator activity

definition.value: Modulates the rate of NTP hydrolysis by a NTPase.

label.value: ATPase regulator activity

definition.value: Modulates the rate of ATP hydrolysis by an ATPase.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter involved in mammary gland formation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter that contributes to the formation of the mammary line, placode or bud.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription initiation from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of a process involved in starting transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: endoribonuclease inhibitor activity

definition.value: Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of an endoribonuclease, any enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis of ester linkages within ribonucleic acid by creating internal breaks.

label.value: deoxyribonuclease inhibitor activity

definition.value: Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of deoxyribonuclease.

label.value: coreceptor activity involved in epidermal growth factor receptor signaling pathway

definition.value: Combining with an extracellular messenger, and in cooperation with a primary EGF receptor, initiating a change in cell activity through the EGF receptor signaling pathway.

label.value: regulation of transcription involved in primary germ layer cell fate commitment

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter that results in cells adopting an endoderm, ectoderm or mesoderm cell fate.

label.value: BMP signaling pathway involved in mesodermal cell fate specification

definition.value: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a member of the BMP (bone morphogenetic protein) family to a receptor on the surface of a target cell, which contributes to a cell becoming specified to adopt a mesodermal fate.

label.value: positive regulation of Wnt signaling pathway by BMP signaling pathway

definition.value: A series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of any member of the BMP (bone morphogenetic protein) family binding to a cell surface receptor that results in an increase in the rate, frequency or extent of a Wnt signaling pathway.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter involved in definitive endodermal cell fate specification

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter that ultimately results in a cell being specified to adopt a definitive endodermal cell fate.

label.value: regulation of transcription involved in lymphatic endothelial cell fate commitment

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter that contributes to the commitment of a venous endothelial cell to a lymphatic endothelial cell.

label.value: regulation of transcription involved in cell fate commitment

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter that contributes to the commitment of a cell to a specific fate.

label.value: regulation of transcription involved in venous endothelial cell fate commitment

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter that contributes to the commitment of a cell to a specific fate and contributes to a cell adopting a venous endothelial cell fate.

label.value: regulation of transcription involved in eye field cell fate commitment of camera-type eye

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter that contributes to the commitment of a neurectodermal cell to a specialized neurectodermal cell that will give rise to the optic vesicle.

label.value: regulation of hair cycle by BMP signaling pathway

definition.value: A series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of any member of the BMP (bone morphogenetic protein) family binding to a cell surface receptor that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the hair cycle.

label.value: negative regulation of chromatin silencing by small RNA

definition.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of chromatin silencing by small RNA. Chromatin silencing by small RNA is the repression of transcription by conversion of large regions of DNA into heterochromatin, directed by small RNAs sharing sequence identity to the repressed region.

label.value: phospholipase D inhibitor activity

definition.value: Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a phospholipase D, an enzyme that catalyzes the reaction -  a phosphatidylcholine + H2O -eq- choline + a phosphatidate.

label.value: regulation of ribosomal protein gene transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the synthesis of RNA from ribosomal protein genes by RNA polymerase II, originating at an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: positive regulation of ribosomal protein gene transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the synthesis of RNA from ribosomal protein genes by RNA polymerase II, originating at an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: lipid tube

definition.value: A macromolecular complex that contains a tube of lipid surrounded by a protein coat.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter involved in kidney development

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter that contributes to the branching morphogenesis by which the kidney progresses from its initial formation to the mature state.

label.value: endopeptidase activator activity

definition.value: Increases the activity of an endopeptidase, any enzyme that hydrolyzes nonterminal peptide bonds in polypeptides.

label.value: peptidase regulator activity

definition.value: Modulates the activity of a peptidase, any enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis peptide bonds.

label.value: endopeptidase regulator activity

definition.value: Modulates the activity of a peptidase, any enzyme that hydrolyzes nonterminal peptide bonds in polypeptides.

label.value: BMP signaling pathway involved in ureter morphogenesis

definition.value: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a member of the BMP (bone morphogenetic protein) family to a receptor on the surface of a target cell, which contributes to the shaping of the ureter. The ureter is a tube that extends from the kidney to the bladder.

label.value: BMP signaling pathway involved in renal system segmentation

definition.value: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a member of the BMP (bone morphogenetic protein) family to a receptor on the surface of a target cell, which contributes to the segmentation of the renal system.

label.value: type I terminal bouton

definition.value: Terminal inflated portion of the axon of a glutamatergic neuron, containing the specialized apparatus necessary to release neurotransmitters that will induce the contraction of muscle. The axon terminus is considered to be the whole region of thickening and the terminal bouton is a specialized region of it.

label.value: type II terminal bouton

definition.value: Terminal inflated portion of the axon of a non-glutamatergic neuron, containing the specialized apparatus necessary to release neurotransmitters at a regulatory synapse. The axon terminus is considered to be the whole region of thickening and the terminal bouton is a specialized region of it.

label.value: type Ib terminal bouton

definition.value: Terminal inflated portion of the axon of a glutamatergic neuron, containing the specialized apparatus necessary for the tonic release neurotransmitters that will induce the contraction of muscle. Type Ib terminal boutons are larger than type Is terminal boutons.

label.value: type Is terminal bouton

definition.value: Terminal inflated portion of the axon of a glutamatergic neuron, containing the specialized apparatus necessary for the phasic release neurotransmitters that will induce the contraction of muscle. Type Is terminal boutons are smaller than type Ib terminal boutons.

label.value: negative regulation of chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette

definition.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate, or extent of chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette. Chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette is the repression of transcription at silent mating-type loci by altering the structure of chromatin.

label.value: regulation of chromatin silencing at rDNA

definition.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the repression of transcription of ribosomal DNA by altering the structure of chromatin.

label.value: negative regulation of chromatin silencing at rDNA

definition.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the repression of transcription of ribosomal DNA by altering the structure of chromatin.
